Package: rardl
Type: Package
Title: Rolling-Window and Recursive ARDL Cointegration Analysis
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("Muhammad", "Alkhalaf", email = "muhammedalkhalaf@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0002-2677-9246"))
Description: Provides rolling-window and recursive implementations of the
    Autoregressive Distributed Lag (ARDL) bounds cointegration test, as
    proposed by Shahbaz, Khan and Mubarak (2023)
    <doi:10.1016/j.eneco.2022.106642> and Khan, Shahbaz and Napari (2023)
    <doi:10.1016/j.eneco.2022.106683>. The package also implements recursive
    ADF unit root testing and recursive Granger causality testing within the
    same framework. Critical values are obtained via Monte Carlo simulation.
    Together, the five analysis types (rolling, recursive, radf, rgranger,
    simulate) allow researchers to detect structural instability in
    cointegrating relationships over time.
